commit.message:
Reduce redundancy in fused type dispatch functions.
Moves the type mappers into separate utility functions that are deduplicated and reused.

Integrate #7101 by using an argument tuple instead of a list to avoid overhead.

See https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/7101
Modernise a bit of code generation.
Add missing "extern" struct type declarations for the fused type mapper functions.
Remove heavy Tempita usage from FusedTypes code generation and use lean f-strings instead.
Use f-strings instead of %-formatting in a few places.
Fix f-string syntax for Cython compilation.
Move a variable declaration to the function where it's used.

milestone.description: First feature release after the cleanup releases 3.0 and 3.1.

title: Reduce redundancy in fused type dispatch functions
